==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filial
<hw>Fil"ial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>filialis</ets>, fr. <ets>filius</ets> son, <ets>filia</ets>
daughter; akin to e. <ets>female</ets>, <ets>feminine</ets>. Cf.
<er>Fitz</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a son or
daughter; becoming to a child in relation to his parents; <as>as,
<ex>filial</ex> obedience</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bearing the relation of a child.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And thus the <qex>filial</qex> Godhead answering spoke.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filially</ent>⟦br⟧
